            <persname source="local">
               <part>Fort Trigo, María Pilar</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
      </did>
      <bioghist id="aspace_b70c1bd511a446a46135970427da9f65">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>María Pilar Fort Trigo died on May 27, 2005 in Valencia at the age of 87, widow of Enrique Jorro Vives.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_aadca41c06aa982377593720fcb4a75a">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Diary of María Pilar Fort Trigo, a woman from Valencia, Spain, covering 1936 October through 1938 January, and lacking 1937 December. The diary describes the everyday life of a Spanish woman during the Spanish Civil War and discusses gender relations in Spain and Fort Trigo's engagement to a lawyer, Enrique Jorro Vives. Also includes Fort Trigo's obituary.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_0f95eac594d6edb09207f85124623c4b">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Transferred by the Librarian for the Latin American and Iberian Collections, 2017. Gift of Kevin Jackson, History Revealed, 2016.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_d16ff400b0e5e3f8283516049fc5379b">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
